A man, aged 40, allegedly beat his partner to death. CAPE TOWN - A man is expected to appear in the Butterworth Magistrates Court in the Eastern Cape on Wednesday in connection with his girlfriend's murder.The 40-year-old suspect allegedly beat his partner to death, using a stick, at the Yako informal settlement earlier this week.The victim died on the scene after sustaining multiple injuries to her body.The police's Jackson Manatha says: He has been charged for the murder. &quot;He will appear before the Butterworth Magistrates Court for murder. Sadly, we cannot reveal the deceased s identity as the majority of her family members have not been informed of her death. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)